    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Sept 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1832</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">By the enclosed letter<lb/> you will find that I have not forgotten
                you<lb/> as you conjectured in your esteemed favour<lb/> per the
                    <persName>Randolph</persName> record on <date>Friday</date><add>?</add>. I<lb/>
                thank you much for your interesting statement<lb/> of the Cholera, and am happy to
                find<lb/> the disease is taking its exit from your<lb/> fine city. You conjecture
                right, that<lb/> it is not properly understoodâ€”we have<lb/> the advantage of the
                experience of all<lb/> the faculty of the <placeName>North</placeName>, doubtless it
                will<lb/> pass over our city, altho' we are prepared<lb/> for its reception it will
                nevertheless be a<lb/> very c<add>?</add> visitor. I have<lb/> certainly been
                detained visiting you on<lb/> account of the ravages it produced<lb/> at the
                    <placeName>North</placeName>. I fear the fall will<lb/> have too far advanced to
                admit<lb/> of my leaving home for a colder region<lb/> however, I anticipate being
                with you<lb/> in the early part of the spring, God</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>being willing, but most certain some time<lb/> during the summer. I was pleased to
                note<lb/> that you think my friends would be pleased<lb/> to see the <hi
                    rend="underline"><persName>Dator</persName></hi><add>?</add>, I assure you none
                more<lb/> so than the <persName>Dater</persName> himself to see his friends.<lb/> I
                must humble you by presenting my friend<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Allen</persName> with the enclosed letter. Should<lb/> you
                    <add>see</add> any of my friends who shall<lb/> inquire, state my reasons for
                not<lb/> being in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>. I shall<lb/> be glad to hear
                from you after<lb/> the holidays, and what assistance<lb/> you had with the prayers
                on <date>Kippur<lb/> Day</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Again I must conclude<lb/> with the best wishes and regard<lb/> of
                your friend.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Jacob De La Motta</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
